text:
Does anyone know if you can filter HubDB tables with Hubl using CRM properties?  I have tried the following two methods and neither have worked.

Method 1
```{% for row in hubdb_table_rows(&lt;table-id&gt;, 'type__eq=MARKETING&amp;ticker__eq={{ deal.ticker }}') %}
    &lt;ul class="portfolio-grid"&gt;
      &lt;li class="document-name"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:viewDocument({{row.box_id}})"&gt;{{ row.name }}&lt;/a&gt; {{row.type}}&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
{% endfor %}```
Method 2
```{% for row in hubdb_table_rows(&lt;table-id&gt;, 'type__eq=MARKETING') %}
  {% if request.query_dict.ticker == {{ deal.ticker }} %}
    &lt;ul class="portfolio-grid"&gt;
      &lt;li class="document-name"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:viewDocument({{row.box_id}})"&gt;{{ row.name }}&lt;/a&gt; {{row.type}}&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}```
